  <description type="morphology">Plants strongly mat-forming, glaucous, often with woody base. Stems erect, 7–25(–30) cm, densely stipitate-glandular distally. Leaves: basal leaves persistent; cauline leaves in 1–3 pairs, abruptly reduced distal to lowest pair; basal blades ascending or often arcuate-spreading, needlelike, (0.5–)1–2.5(–3.5) cm × 0.5–1.5 mm, rigid, herbaceous, apex spinose, glabrous to puberulent, glaucous. Inflorescences 5–25+-flowered, open cymes. Pedicels 3–25 mm, stipitate-glandular. Flowers: sepals 1–3-veined, lateral veins less developed or all obscure, ovate, 3–4.5 mm, to 6 mm in fruit, margins broad, apex usually obtuse to rounded, abruptly acute, sparsely to densely stipitate-glandular; petals white, obovate to oblanceolate, 4.5–10 mm, 1.5–3 times as long as sepals, apex rounded; nectaries as lateral and abaxial rounding, with slight lateral expansion, at base of filaments opposite sepals, 0.3 mm. Capsules 5–9 mm, glabrous. Seeds yellowish tan to gray, ellipsoid-oblong, 1.8–2.5(–3.2) mm, tuberculate; tubercles rounded, elongate. 2n = 22.</description>
